<subSubSection pageNumber="268" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="268">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="268">Note:</emphasis>
Redhead &amp; Kuyper (in Laursen &amp; al., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="268">Arctic Alpine Mycol.</emphasis>
2: 326. 1987) selected the cited Micheli plate as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
but this choice was rejected by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
&amp; Ryman (1989) in favour of a Rudbeck drawing because the Micheli element was excluded by Fries, the sanctioning author. Redhead &amp; Kuyper (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="268">Taxon</emphasis>
42: 447. 1993) argued that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
&amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ryman’s">Ryman's</normalizedToken>
choice was ineligible but 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jørgensen">Jorgensen</normalizedToken>
&amp; Ryman (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="268">l.c.</emphasis>
43: 253-255. 1994) refuted this argument and designated an 
<typeStatus>epitype</typeStatus>
in support of their own type choice (the Rudbeck figure).
</paragraph>
